## Portia AI: What it is and why we use it

Portia is an open-source developer framework for building transparent, steerable, and authenticated AI agents. It provides planning, stateful execution, and secure tool integrations so agents can reliably perform multi-step work with human-in-the-loop clarifications and just-in-time auth. See: [docs](https://docs.portialabs.ai/?utm_source=openai), [homepage](https://www.portialabs.ai/).

### Core ideas
- **Planning**: Multi-shot prompter elicits an explicit step-by-step plan with tools, inputs, and outputs per step. [docs](https://docs.portialabs.ai/?utm_source=openai)
- **Execution**: A plan executes as a `PlanRun`, tracking state, results, and any required clarifications. [docs](https://docs.portialabs.ai/?utm_source=openai)
- **Clarifications**: Structured prompts to collect missing inputs, approvals, or auth from a human or another system. [guide](https://docs.portialabs.ai/handle-auth-clarifications?utm_source=openai)
- **Tools**: Natural-language callable integrations with schemas and a `run` implementation. Bring-your-own or use Portia’s catalog (Google, GitHub, Slack, Zendesk, etc.). [intro](https://docs.portialabs.ai/intro-to-tools?utm_source=openai), [catalog](https://docs.portialabs.ai/portia-tools?utm_source=openai), [open-source tools](https://docs.portialabs.ai/portia-tools/open-source/?utm_source=openai)
- **Authentication**: Extensible, secure, token-refreshing JIT auth for tool calls; supports OAuth-backed SaaS tools. [guide](https://docs.portialabs.ai/handle-auth-clarifications?utm_source=openai)
- **Cloud optionality**: Use the open-source SDK locally; add Portia Cloud for storage, hosted tools, and a dashboard. [setup](https://docs.portialabs.ai/setup-account?utm_source=openai)

## Quick start

### Requirements
- Python 3.11+

### Install SDK
```bash
pip install portia-sdk-python
# or with extra providers
pip install "portia-sdk-python[all]"
```
Refs: [install](https://docs.portialabs.ai/install?utm_source=openai)

### Configure LLM provider
Set env vars for your chosen LLM. Example for OpenAI:
```bash
export OPENAI_API_KEY="<your-openai-key>"
```
Refs: [install](https://docs.portialabs.ai/install?utm_source=openai)

### Sanity check (CLI)
```bash
portia-cli run "add 1 + 2"
```
Expect a completed `PlanRun` and a final output of 3. Refs: [install](https://docs.portialabs.ai/install?utm_source=openai)

## Using Portia Cloud (optional)
Benefits: hosted tools, plan run storage, dashboard (history, users/orgs, API keys).

1) Create an account and generate an API key in the dashboard.
2) Set the API key:
```bash
export PORTIA_API_KEY="<your-portia-api-key>"
```
Refs: [account setup](https://docs.portialabs.ai/setup-account?utm_source=openai)

## Abstractions to know
- **Tool**: Name, description, input/output schemas, and a `run` method. Use for wrapping APIs, local capabilities, or cloud services. Refs: [intro to tools](https://docs.portialabs.ai/intro-to-tools?utm_source=openai)
- **Plan**: Model-produced structured steps based on the user goal.
- **PlanRun**: Tracks execution of the plan, including intermediate results, clarifications, and final outputs.
- **Clarification**: Structured input request when information or approval is missing; commonly used for auth flows and required parameters. Refs: [clarifications & auth](https://docs.portialabs.ai/handle-auth-clarifications?utm_source=openai)

## Tooling highlights (selected)
- **Browser**: Navigate to URLs and complete general web tasks. [open-source tools](https://docs.portialabs.ai/portia-tools/open-source/?utm_source=openai)
