- **Extract / PDF Reader**: Pull content, images, metadata from webpages and PDFs. [open-source tools](https://docs.portialabs.ai/portia-tools/open-source/?utm_source=openai)
- **Image Understanding**: OCR and image Q&A support. [open-source tools](https://docs.portialabs.ai/portia-tools/open-source/?utm_source=openai)
- **Search / Weather**: Utility tools for quick info. [open-source tools](https://docs.portialabs.ai/portia-tools/open-source/?utm_source=openai)
- **SaaS integrations**: GitHub, Google Workspace (Gmail, Drive, Docs, Sheets, Calendar), Microsoft Outlook, Slack, Zendesk, and more. [catalog](https://docs.portialabs.ai/portia-tools?utm_source=openai)

## Environment variables (common)
- `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `MISTRAL_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_API_KEY` (per chosen LLM provider) — set one or more as needed. [install](https://docs.portialabs.ai/install?utm_source=openai)
- `PORTIA_API_KEY` — for Portia Cloud features. [account setup](https://docs.portialabs.ai/setup-account?utm_source=openai)

## Development guidance for this project
- Favor explicit, tool-driven plans for repeatability and auditability.
- Model prompts should request: tools to use, inputs expected, outputs produced at each step.
- Use clarifications whenever an input is missing, risky, or requires human approval.
- Prefer authenticated tools for SaaS access; rely on JIT auth and token refresh.
- Start local-first with the SDK; adopt Cloud for persistence and hosted tools when needed.

